As a result, his son has to takeover the front staff role and that cause an insufficient staffing for the kitchen end and client often need to do overtime under such condition. 
However, the client is able to find one now and he paid the FT front staff $4K-$5K and his son is back helping out the kitchen and now kitchen is more relieved. Client decided to cancel our service since he thinks paying our service reduce his profit and he can save around $900/month. 
For the client, the front staff is a must have and can do more than just taking calls, while our service only take phone calls. 

Client said his son does not like to do front staff and both him and his wife English not good, cannot do the front staff job either. Therefore, they must hire a front staff and the cost of hiring one is high nowadays, otherwise, no one want to work for them. 

I emphasized our value to the client including we have the client's best interest, save front staff training time, no abandoned calls or we call back in a timely manner providing great customer experience which his front staff might not willing to do. 

Based on all the context clues, ideally it is best for the client to have both front staff and our service (since our service help the front staff focus more on Dine-In/Walk-In customers and packaging, instead of multitasking taking calls while doing other duties simultaneously. 

The client said if the front staff quit, he will need our service again. I told the client that there will be $50+ license fee for suspension, but the client does not want to pay it. As a result, the client decided to cancel our service instead and is informed about the $2000 reinstallation fee.
